Exercise
Guess the type
To find out the type of a value or a variable that refers to that value, you can use the type() function. Suppose you've defined a variable a, but you forgot the type of this variable. To determine the type of a, simply execute:

type(a)
We already went ahead and created three variables: a, b and c. You can use the IPython shell to discover their type. Which of the following options is correct?

Instructions
50 XP
Possible answers

type(a)

type(b)

type(c)


Option A: a is of type int, b is of type str, c is of type bool

Option B: a is of type float, b is of type bool, c is of type str

Option C: a is of type float, b is of type str, c is of type bool

Option D: a is of type int, b is of type bool, c is of type str

Ans: Option C: a is of type float, b is of type str, c is of type bool